In [80]:
def denorm(image, mean, std):
    mean = torch.tensor(mean).reshape(3, 1, 1)
    std = torch.tensor(std).reshape(3, 1, 1)
    return image * std + mean

def show_images(images, title, mean, std):
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(8, 8, figsize=(10, 10))
    fig.suptitle(title)
    plt.setp(plt.gcf().get_axes(), xticks=[], yticks=[])
    for i, ax in enumerate(axes.flat):
        img = denorm(images[i][0], mean, std)
        img = img.numpy().transpose(1, 2, 0)
        ax.text(0, 1, f'{dataset_classes[images[i][1]]}', size=10, color='red')
        ax.imshow((img * 255).astype('uint8'))

Построение архитектуры свёрточной сети¶

In [83]:
class ResBlock(nn.Sequential):
    def __init__(self, in_, out):
        super(ResBlock, self).__init__(
            torch.nn.Conv2d(in_, out, kernel_size=3, padding=1),
            torch.nn.BatchNorm2d(out),
            torch.nn.ReLU(inplace=True)
        )
In [84]:
class ResNet(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self):
        super(ResNet, self).__init__()
        self.conv1 = ResBlock(3, 64)
        self.layer1 = nn.Sequential(ResBlock(64, 64), ResBlock(64, 64))
        self.conv_and_mp1 = nn.Sequential(ResBlock(64, 128), nn.MaxPool2d(kernel_size=3))
        self.conv_and_mp2 = nn.Sequential(ResBlock(128, 256), nn.MaxPool2d(kernel_size=3))
        self.layer2 = nn.Sequential(ResBlock(256, 256), ResBlock(256, 256))
        self.conv_and_mp3 = nn.Sequential(ResBlock(256, 512), nn.MaxPool2d(kernel_size=3))
        self.lin = torch.nn.Sequential(torch.nn.Flatten(), torch.nn.Linear(512, len(classes)))

    def forward(self, x):
        out = self.conv1(x)
        out = self.layer1(out) + out
        out = self.conv_and_mp1(out)
        out = self.conv_and_mp2(out)
        out = self.layer2(out) + out
        out = self.conv_and_mp3(out)
        out = self.lin(out)
        return out

      (2): ReLU(inplace=True)
    )
    (1): ResBlock(
      (0): Conv2d(64, 64, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (1): BatchNorm2d(64, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
      (2): ReLU(inplace=True)
    )
  )
  (conv_and_mp1): Sequential(
    (0): ResBlock(
      (0): Conv2d(64, 128, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (1): BatchNorm2d(128, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
      (2): ReLU(inplace=True)
    )
    (1): MaxPool2d(kernel_size=3, stride=3, padding=0, dilation=1, ceil_mode=False)
  )
  (conv_and_mp2): Sequential(
    (0): ResBlock(
      (0): Conv2d(128, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (1): BatchNorm2d(256, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
      (2): ReLU(inplace=True)
    )
    (1): MaxPool2d(kernel_size=3, stride=3, padding=0, dilation=1, ceil_mode=False)
  )
  (layer2): Sequential(
    (0): ResBlock(
      (0): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (1): BatchNorm2d(256, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
      (2): ReLU(inplace=True)
    )
    (1): ResBlock(
      (0): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (1): BatchNorm2d(256, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
      (2): ReLU(inplace=True)
    )
  )
  (conv_and_mp3): Sequential(
    (0): ResBlock(
      (0): Conv2d(256, 512, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (1): BatchNorm2d(512, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
      (2): ReLU(inplace=True)
    )
    (1): MaxPool2d(kernel_size=3, stride=3, padding=0, dilation=1, ceil_mode=False)
  )
  (lin): Sequential(
    (0): Flatten(start_dim=1, end_dim=-1)
    (1): Linear(in_features=512, out_features=10, bias=True)
  )

In [88]:
def get_accuracy(model, data_loader, device):
    tp, n = 0, 0
    with torch.no_grad():
        for images, labels in data_loader:
            labels = labels.to(device)
            images = images.to(device)
            outputs = model(images)
            _, predicted = torch.max(outputs.data, 1)
            n += labels.size(0)
            tp += (predicted == labels).sum()
    return tp / n

def get_loss(model, data_loader, device):
    loss, n = 0, 0
    with torch.no_grad():
        for images, labels in data_loader:
            labels = labels.to(device)
            images = images.to(device)
            outputs = model(images)
            loss += loss_function(outputs, labels)
            n += labels.size(0)
    return loss / n

def accuracy(outputs, labels):
    _, predicted = torch.max(outputs.data, 1)
    return torch.tensor(torch.sum(predicted == labels).item() / len(predicted))

def train(model, data_loader, epochs, loss_function, optimizer, device):
    print(' ')
    start = time.time()
    for epoch in range(epochs):
        t1 = time.time()
        accs, lss = [], []
        for i, (images, labels) in enumerate(data_loader):
            labels = labels.to(device)
            images = images.to(device)
            optimizer.zero_grad()
            outputs = model(images)
            loss = loss_function(outputs, labels)
            acc = accuracy(outputs, labels)
            lss.append(loss)
            accs.append(acc)
            loss.backward()
            optimizer.step()
        t2 = time.time()
        print(f'\n {epoch + 1}:  = {torch.stack(lss).mean()},  = {torch.stack(accs).mean()},  = {t2 - t1}')
    end = time.time()
    print('\n   {}'.format(end - start))
